Arthur C. Clarke wrote the short story &quot;The Songs from distant Earth&quot; in 1958. Almost three decades later in 1986 he extended the story to a novel bearing the same name. Mike Oldfield was quite impressed with the novel, which is ending in a musical concert and he contacted Arthur C. Clarke, beause he wanted to compose a music for this book. The result is here, hope you will enjoy it. Arthur C. Clarke, impressed by the music Mike wrote for the movie &quot;Tke Killing Fields&quot;, stated that Mike has lived to his expectations...

